:white_check_mark: iphydf
:x: irungentoo
You have signed the CLA already but the status is still pending? Let us [recheck](https://cla-assistant.io/check/TokTok/c-toxcore?pullRequest=918) it.

>Files changed: 0

I'm confused. We already have fix for this in our repo.

Is this just for the sake of having this exact commit hash in the repo?
Yes. Every time I look at the toktok repo and I see "1 commit behind irungentoo/master", I need to remember which commit that was, and that we already have that change.
So, what will happen if irungentoo makes 20 more commits? We will merge them too?
This just doesn't make much sense to me.
Yes, if irungentoo makes 20 commits tomorrow, we will merge them following our regular review process.

Why not merge 20 commits, if they are useful? If useless, we may not merge them.
But I don't see any reason to merge empty commit
IMO we can merge this, it's also slightly annoying me.
This commit isn't useful in any way. Why pay attention to a repository that isn't maintained?

Does this commit harm in any way? Why are we spending 3 days discussing it? irungentoo/toxcore obviously is maintained. Security fixes are ported back to it. It's frozen otherwise, but its security status is maintained.
I don't mind if you merge this. I just wanted to know if you think it's a good idea to pay attention to every small change that happens in irungentoo/toxcore.

Yes, I do think that we should pay attention to every small change in iru/toxcore, especially because nothing happens there, so *if* something happens, it must be important. If I see "behind iru/toxcore", I'll want to check what happened there. This PR makes it so I don't need to think about it anymore, until the next (likely important) change happens.
